  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Equip Rescue Teams to Save Tiger and Human Lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The incidence of human-tiger conflicts is a growing matter of concern in India. As per published data over 800 cases of human casualties have been recorded in the last 20 years. West Bengal (445) and Uttar Pradesh (161) states, top the list in such casualties. They invariably come into conflict with humans as most forest patches are fragmented by human habitations. In 2016 alone more than 30 tigers have lost their lives due to retaliatory action. It is important to address the issue swiftly.</narrative>
  </description>
